					<li>(0.5,0.03)</li>
				</offsets>
			</li>
		</modExtensions>
		
		<comps>
			<li Class="MVCF.Comps.CompProperties_VerbProps">
				<compClass>MVCF.Comps.Comp_VerbProps</compClass>
				<verbProps>
					<li>
						<label>MPi-KM-72</label>
						<canBeToggled>true</canBeToggled>
						<separateToggle>false</separateToggle>
					</li>
					<li>
						<label>GP-25</label>
						<canBeToggled>true</canBeToggled>
						<separateToggle>false</separateToggle>
						<description>Caliber: 40mm VOG-25. 1-round tube. Single shot.					
The GP-25 is a Russian 40mm grenade launcher designed in the 1960s, as part of several independent worldwide efforts to replace the need for rifle grenades. It can be fitted onto almost every major AK variant that exists, as well as a few non-AK rifles (such as the AN-94.) Other derivatives of the GP-25 include the later GP-30 and GP-34.</description>
					</li>
				</verbProps>
			</li>
		</comps>
		<generateCommonality>0.05</generateCommonality> <!-- Uncommon -->
